                <head>No. 3.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Phelps</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-10-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 26, 1888</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Bayard states that Lord Sackville, in his correspondence and in frequent
                    interviews intended to be published, has impugned the motives of the President
                    and the Senate in regard to Canadian questions, and that his usefulness in this
                    country is at an end. A strong public sentiment has been aroused, and Lord
                    Salisbury should be permitted as speedily as possible to understand the
                    necessity of immediate action.</p>
            </div>
